    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The main idea of the project is to have a few submodules to help the mainline compilation in the general case. In the situation where you are trying to cross compile, these submodules will no longer compile cleanly because, as you said, things are too case-specific. So the best course of action is to clone the repository without submodules, and always use all of the system-wide dependencies.\r\n\r\nDoes this answer your question ?"
